info.senderName: NWS Aberdeen (Northern and Northeastern South Dakota)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 16 at 8:36AM CDT until further notice by NWS Aberdeen
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Aberdeen SD has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Minnesota... Mustinka River Near Wheaton affecting Traverse County. .Warm temperatures will melt lingering snowpack and increase river flows. ...FLOOD WARNING FOR SNOWMELT IN EFFECT FROM THIS MORNING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Mustinka River Near Wheaton. * WHEN...From this morning until further notice. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:30 AM CDT Sunday the stage was 93.2 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 7:30 AM CDT Sunday was 93.2 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 92.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov/abr. The next statement will be issued Monday afternoon by 445 PM CDT.
